# DECISIONS.log — Huminic Studio launch closeout

**Format:** append-only. One entry per non-trivial choice, workaround, assumption confirmation, or risk resolution. Timestamps in ISO 8601 UTC.

Entry types:
- `ACK` — session-start re-acknowledgment of ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA.md and PLAN.md hashes
- `DEC` — decision the agent took with rationale
- `CHANGE` — explicit edit to a governance file (ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA / PLAN / etc.) explaining the change
- `WORKAROUND` — temporary adaptation with reason + reversibility
- `BLOCKER` — discovery that cannot be closed in this run; surfaced with owner + next step
- `OP-GATE` — operator action awaited; what is blocked; what is unblocked

---

## 2026-06-01

### 2026-06-01T07:30:00Z DEC closeout-checkpoint-initiated

Operator (Duane Wells) issued the final closeout + verification + launch-readiness mandate. Agent entered the Section 0.5 planning-mode checkpoint per the prompt. Six artifacts produced in this turn: `PLAN.md`, `ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA.md`, `AGENTS.md` (session-start hook), `HUMAN_TESTING_SCRIPT.md`, `AUTONOMOUS_TESTING_PLAN.md`, `CHECKPOINT_PROOF.md`. Stale/competing documents archived to `docs/archive/2026-06-01/`. issues.md absorbed into PLAN.md and archived.

### 2026-06-01T07:30:00Z DEC dealer-universe-resolved

The "5 of 6 missing" ambiguity from prior notes was off by one. The canonical launch-scope dealer slugs are: `serra-honda` (already has tester auth), `serra-nissan`, `serra-service`, `tony-serra-ford`, `ford-of-columbia`, `hyundai-of-columbia`, `serra-automotive`. Six need new auth.yaml in P-CZ-002; the seventh (serra-honda) keeps the legacy `tester` account or gets a refresh during P-CZ-002 at operator discretion. `cedar-ridge-automotive` stays as a fixture per D-019; not part of launch-scope dealer universe. `huminic-motors` (P-CZ-003) is a separate canary, not in the dealer universe. Recorded in `docs/launch/CHECKPOINT_PROOF.md` Section A.

